It is very rare for an algorithm to fit better than Levenberg-Marquardt,
This example shows how to construct a test to determine if this is true.

SSQABS = 7.31E-03 for the fitting algorithm Levenberg-Marquardt
Coefficients: [ 0.87519  0.31626  0.01557 -3.66802]
Algorithm NelderMead did not fit better than Levenberg-Marquardt.
Algorithm Powell did not fit better than Levenberg-Marquardt.
Algorithm CG did not fit better than Levenberg-Marquardt.
Algorithm BFGS did not fit better than Levenberg-Marquardt.
Algorithm Newton-CG did not fit better than Levenberg-Marquardt.
Algorithm Anneal did not fit better than Levenberg-Marquardt.
Algorithm COBYLA did not fit better than Levenberg-Marquardt.
Algorithm SLSQP did not fit better than Levenberg-Marquardt.
